e and several hybrids. Of Pinus there are 8 species, and of Hicoria about the same, or more if they were better understood. Only 2 well-marked species (shrubs) are confined to Alabama: Xeviusia alabameusis Gray and Croton alabamensis E. A. Smith. But there are at least 30 alleged species of Crataegus and a few of Primus and Tilia known only from Alabama specimens. || ABSTRACT AUTHORS: R. M. Harper
